<br>
Quoted:<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> First of all, I was probably the hibbie he saw port in :P<br>
<br>
one of our rogues was playing with climbing on Dagda and suddenly went &quot;WTF? theres a seige ram here!&quot;. we were currently hunting near Cain and ran over to check it out, but we saw that the sea of guards outside were intact. We had assumed that she meant the ram was OUTSIDE so we scouted around outside the walls and found nothing, then ported in and found the ram. We killed the ram, CLICKED ON THE DOORS and they were at FULL HEALTH. and thought nothing more of it. We assumed it was some idiot with too much money goofing off, since ALL GUARDS AND DOORS were INTACT at the time and there wasnt anyone else (visible) there. People build Rams in the middle of TNN all the time, we figured this guy did the same just in the middle of nowhere for some odd reason.<br>
<br>
Now if seige weapons said which realm built them, it would be a TOTALLY DIFFERENT STORY. but nooo... all we got was &quot;you target the seige ram&quot; :P. We tried to figure out which realm it came from but when we got no info, we assumed Hibernian.<br>
<br>
needless to say we're kicking ourselves in the ass for not checking back again later :P, but we hunted RIGHT BESIDE THE FREAKING FORT all night (until we saw that the relic had turned to neutral, which is when we ran to emain to block the milegates) and didn't see a single disturbance outside.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
